13:
I made a shameless display of
myself during my previous outing
with Lady Phiria.
15:
However, that incident did provide 
me with some insight... It would 
appear my way of thinking 
is a tad obtuse.
18:
My knowledge and experiences are
those of a knight, but that is no
longer my station in life. I'm fully
aware of this, and yet...
22:
Hm... I understand your plight all too
well. So, what is this training you
speak of?
27:
I must become more flexible as a
person. Therefore, it is imperative
that I... learn to have fun!
30:
Could I possibly request your
assistance in this matter?
35:
Thank you for helping us catch the
criminal! We'll see you around!
38:
Catching a shoplifter, busting an
illegal street stall, helping a lost
child, and stopping a pickpocket...
You've had one heck of a day,
Cecilia.
43:
My apologies... We were supposed
to be having fun, but I kept
interrupting us...
47:
Y-you don't need to apologize. We
helped a lot of people!
52: But I am still as obstinate as ever.
54:
And I'm beginning to think... that will
never change...
64:
Hngh! A-Arum, p-please... Not so
tight!
68:
Hey there. Didn't expect to see you
guys here.
76:
What's with the long face? You and
Phiria have a fight or something?
85:
You're aware that the fact you're
even worrying about this is proof
that you're uptight, right?
92:
What's the big deal anyway? So
what if you're a bit of a square?
94:
You get along with Phiria just fine,
right? I don't see the problem.
98:
But Lady Phiria has changed. She's
become so strong.
101:
In contrast... I'm embarrassed to say
that I have not changed in the
slightest.
109:
That is very likely, but... That does not
stop me from worrying.
111:
Despite my status as a knight, I am
weaker than Lady Phiria. I am a
fraud
119:
You're the one supposed to be
protecting them, but you're too
weak to actually do it! It pisses you
off, doesn't it?
123:
I-I don't know if I would phrase it in
that way, but...
127:
Yeah, but I think I'm fighting those
feelings a bit more than you. I guess
I think of them as a reason to get
stronger.
130: Sisty, I got it! I bought it all by myself!
134:
Yes, yes, good job... How are you
holding up, Light?
139:
Hehe... Pay me no mind... I am just...
an adorable little doll...
142:
My bad. I shouldn't have forced
Arum on you.
147: I think you're a fine big sister.
161:
I betrayed the army, took Arum, and
escaped. We wouldn't be here if it
weren't for my actions.
165:
I don't know if that makes me a
good big sister, but I know it makes
me pretty impressive in my own
right.
167: Wouldn't the same go for you?
172:
Heh... I suppose my actions up until
now are rather unbecoming of a
knight.
176:
Exactly. So there's no need to
change. Take pride in what you've
done and keep doing things your
way.
181: Pride... A reason to get stronger...
183:
She really is an extraordinary
person...
